 ('404', '226', 'it', 'Pinko Pallino', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'us', '2016-09-23 22:45:36', '2016-11-17 22:27:34', '366e0b5b-5d08-414c-97e0-b586a01d6004'),
 ('405', '227', 'en_us', 'Paonazzo', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Paonazzo is our grand reserve wine produced by Poggio la Noce. Unlike all the other wines at Poggio la noce which are produced with more than 90% of Sangiovese grapes, Paonazzo is a blend of 50% Sangiovese and 50% Colorino. It is produced from the oldest parcel of the Poggio la Noce single vineyard and only 100 cases are produced. It is an explosive, stunning blend that boasts a deeply ruby color. It is a wine of immense structure and it’s meant for serious cellaring.&nbsp; Coming soon!</p>', '<p>Vineyard: La Noce vineyard on the property of POGGIO LA NOCE, Fiesole and San Casciano (Province of Florence, Tuscany, Italy).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Altitude: 800 ft elavation, 250 meters above sea level</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Orientation: South - South West facing</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Vineyard Size: 5 acres</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Year Planted: Partly in 2000 and partly in 2006 for the Sangiovese. 25-30 years aged vines for the Colorino.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Soil: Medium-textured, predominantly calcareous marl breakdown of alberese and galestro strata, with abundant gravel-rocky mixture.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Training System: Spur-pruned cordon </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Grapes: 50% Sangiovese, 50% Colorino.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Harvest: Typically end of September to the first ten days of October depending on the season. The Paonazzo grapes benefit from the most hang time allowing for greater phenological maturity and concentration. They are handpicked and brought immediately to the cellar for further selection.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Vinification: After careful cluster selection, followed by gentle destemming, the berries fall on the sorting table where they are sorted individually, allowing only the perfect berries to make it into the fermentation vat. Fermentation takes place in temperature controlled stainless steel vats and typically occurs naturally using the grapes own indigenous yeasts. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Ageing: The wine will age in French oak barriques (225L each) for 24 months depending. Our barriques come from some of the best tonneleries in France and are typically fine grain medium toast. We use a mixture of new and used barriques to avoid excessive wood accent. Following the aging in barriques, the wine is further aged in bottle for two to three years.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Bottles Produced: 600 bottles.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Alcohol: 14%</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Potential Cellaring: 20+ years</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Coming soon!</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Paonazzo is our grand reserve wine, a blend of 50% Sangiovese and 50% Colorino.  It is a wine of immense structure and it’s meant for serious cellaring.', NULL, '2016-09-23 22:46:40', '2016-11-17 22:22:25', '1751aa19-029a-4c6a-8ac4-46283e699b14'),
 ('406', '227', 'it', 'Paonazzo', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paonazzo è la gran riserva\r\nprodotto da Poggio la Noce. A differenza degli altri vini rossi di Poggio La\r\nNoce che sono prodotti con oltre il 90% di uve Sangiovese, Paonazzo è un blend di\r\n50% Sangiovese e 50% Colorino del Val d’Arno. L’uva per Paonazzo viene raccolta\r\ndalla parcella più vecchia del nostro vigneto e ne vengono prodotte soltanto\r\n100 casse. Si tratta di un blend di sorprendente prorompenza, che vanta di un\r\ncolore rosso rubino profondo. Vellutato, di grande classe e concentrazione, che\r\nabbina eleganza a robustezza, Paonazzo offre grande struttura ed è un vino di\r\ngrande longevità.</p>', '<p>Verrà rilasciato a breve!</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Paonazzo è la gran riserva di Poggio la Noce, un blend di 50% Sangiovese e 50% Colorino del Val d’Arno. Paonazzo offre grande struttura ed è un vino di grande longevità.', NULL, '2016-09-23 22:46:40', '2016-11-15 09:26:16', 'a60c9428-d7e3-4e9a-93db-282773ca2c9c'),
