 ('452', '269', 'en_us', 'Bàja', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Baja\r\nis a Falanghina from the Campi Flegrei area, selected and produced for Poggio\r\nla Noce, right in the heart of the Campi Flegrei area outside of Naples, from a\r\nvineyard located on a promontory surrounded by sea. Born out of a selection of\r\nthe best falanghina grapes, Baja has deep mineral notes combined with elegant\r\nfruitiness, and the surprising saltiness of the sea. These are the classic\r\ncharacteristics of an exceptional Falanghina, which make it the perfect\r\naccompaniment to seafood.</p>', '<p>Vineyard: Campi Flegrei, Baia, Naples.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Altitude:&nbsp;50 to 150&nbsp;meters above sea level</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Orientation:&nbsp;South West facing </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vineyard Size:&nbsp;0.5 hectares</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Year Planted:&nbsp;25 to 50 year old vines</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Soil:&nbsp;\r\nOf\r\nvolcanic origin with sandy soil characterized by a strong presence of ash and\r\nlapilli</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Training System:&nbsp;Double Guyot </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Grapes: Falanghina </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Harvest:&nbsp;Typically, around the 20th to the 22nd of September The Gigetto grapes are picked first as we are trying to make a fresh fruit driven final wine. They are picked at optimal maturity level but with less emphasis on concentration. They are handpicked and brought immediately to the cellar for further selection).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vinification:&nbsp;After careful cluster selection, followed by gentle destemming, the berries fall on the sorting table where they are sorted individually allowing only the perfect berries to make it into the Gigetto fermentation vat. Fermentation takes place in temperature controlled stainless steel vats and typically occurs naturally using the grapes own indigenous yeasts. The Sangiovese grapes and Teroldego grapes are each vinified separately so that they may be blended later. Blending decisions will vary depending on the years, with the percentage Teroldego varying between Gigiò and Gigetto.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ageing:&nbsp;The wine will age in oak botti (1000L barrels) for a few months, up to 6 months depending on the year. Our botti come from one of the best Italian tonnelerie and are typically fine grain medium toast. We use a mixture of new and used large size botti to avoid any excessive wood accent. Following the aging in botti, the wine is further aged in bottle for 6 months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bottles Produced:&nbsp;4000 bottles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alcohol:&nbsp;13% to 14%</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Potential Cellaring:&nbsp;Easily 5 years</p>', NULL, NULL, '[]', '[]', 'Baja is a Falanghina from the Campi Flegrei area, selected and produced for Poggio la Noce.', NULL, '2016-11-10 17:59:36', '2016-11-11 11:45:49', '3ddca496-8d17-4f80-9e8f-a71726828041'),
 ('453', '269', 'it', 'Bàja', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Bàja\r\nè una Falanghina DOC dei Campi Flegrei, selezionata e prodotta per Poggio la\r\nNoce, proprio nel cuore dei Campi Flegrei, da un vigneto posto su un\r\npromontorio circondato dal mare. Per Bàja viene effettuata una selezione delle\r\nmigliori uve riscontrando nel vino delle profonde note minerali che si uniscono\r\nal fruttato dell\'uva e infine il salato del mare: queste sono le\r\ncaratteristiche di una eccezionale falanghina. Bàja si abbina bene con pesce,\r\nfromaggi freschi, fritture di mare.</p>', '<p>Vigneto:&nbsp;Campi\r\nFlegrei, Baia, NA</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Altitudine:&nbsp;50 a 150\r\nmetri sul livello del mare</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Esposizione:&nbsp;Sud-Ovest</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dimensione vigneto:&nbsp;mezzo ettari</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eta dei viti:&nbsp;25\r\na 50 anni, piede franco.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terreno:&nbsp;Di\r\norigine vulcanica con franco sabbioso caratterizzato da una forte presenza di\r\nceneri e lapilli </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Potatura:&nbsp;Guyot\r\nBilaterale</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Uvaggio:&nbsp;Falanghina</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vendemmia:&nbsp;Intorno a metà\r\nsettembre. Le uve di Bàja\r\nsono raccolte a mano e mantenute sotto ghiaccio secco fino a pressatura. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vinificazione:&nbsp;Fermentazione\r\na temperatura controllata con Lieviti naturali.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Invecchiamento:&nbsp;Affinamento\r\nin acciaio per sei mesi sur lies. Susseguente affinamento in bottiglia per\r\naltri 12 mesi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bottiglie prodotte:&nbsp;1000&nbsp;bottiglie.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alcol:&nbsp;13% </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Potenziale invecchiamento:&nbsp;5 anni.</p>', NULL, NULL, '[]', '[]', 'Bàja è una Falanghina DOC dei Campi Flegrei, selezionata e prodotta per Poggio la Noce', NULL, '2016-11-10 17:59:36', '2016-11-15 09:38:37', '6d504d90-39eb-42c9-80d3-17156093645d'),
