 ('269', 'field', '13', 'en_us', ' baja is a falanghina from the campi flegrei area selected and produced for poggio la noce right in the heart of the campi flegrei area outside of naples from a vineyard located on a promontory surrounded by sea born out of a selection of the best falanghina grapes baja has deep mineral notes combined with elegant fruitiness and the surprising saltiness of the sea these are the classic characteristics of an exceptional falanghina which make it the perfect accompaniment to seafood '),
 ('269', 'field', '15', 'en_us', ' south west falanghina of volcanic origin with sandy soil characterized by a strong presence of ash and lapilli campi flegrei area outside of naples fermentation takes place in temperature controlled stainless steel vats after fermentation has taken place the wine will rest on its lees for another 6 months before bottling the wine will age in stainless steel for 6 months and age further in bottle for another year falanghina doc campi flegrei '),
